      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The quality of handles may ultimately provide the quickest test of whether a new building is good or not. If the designer has truly thought about accommodating the human hand and psyche in designing comfortable door handles and other features on a ‘graspable’ scale, then they have probably paid the same attention to guarantee the affordance of other elements such as room shape, ceiling height, indoor lighting, circulation realms, etc. The opposite is also valid: an uncomfortable door handle probably indicates that the entire building in all its details is non-accommodating.",
